answers.body_markdown:
If your data is **everytime** on two lines, you can do this :

```html
&lt;div&gt; innerHTML=&quot;{{ get.content.split(&#39;\n&#39;)[1] }}&quot; &lt;/div&gt;
```

Otherwise, you could write a `Pipe` which truncates the string using Regular Expression :

```html
&lt;div innerHtml=&quot;{{ get.content | iframe }}&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
```

```typescript
import { Pipe, PipeTransform } from &#39;@angular/core&#39;;

@Pipe({name: &#39;iframe&#39;})
export class IframePipe implements PipeTransform {
  transform(text: string): string {
    let regexp = new RegExp(&#39;&lt;iframe.*&lt;\/iframe&gt;&#39;);
    let result = regexp.exec(text);
    return result.length &gt; 0 ? result[0] : &#39;&#39;;
  }
}
```

